reviews.text:
隱身在老牌四星酒店裡，離灣仔站步行約3-5分鐘。

招牌是脆皮烤乳豬，中午提供港式飲茶。

雞子戈炸-據說在港會做的餐廳不超過五家，雞腎加高湯打成泥再煮稠後，加粉凍過後切塊炸過，夾起時有如嫩雞蛋的ㄉㄨㄞㄉㄨㄞ韻律感，入口後卡士達般細緻滑順的香味在口中散開，是一道相當費工的料理。

脆皮乳豬全體-每桌必點菜。豬皮片的大小一致，食用時先取麵皮，抹上乳豬醬或砂糖，覆上豬皮，可搭配蔥球、醃黃瓜、紅蘿蔔，豬皮烤的鬆、脆、酥、透，無韌感，待皮用完後，將乳豬分骨及肉後再度上桌，可選擇選擇手拿豬骨慢慢啃食或者肥嫩油花的乳豬肉，環肥燕瘦任君挑選。

薑汁炒芥蘭-切的大小入口剛好，清脆爽口。

龍崗鹹切雞-使用肉質滑嫩，雞味較濃的龍崗雞，蘸上蔥蒜醬，類似油雞口感。

脆皮烤乳豬為外面餐廳一倍的價格，價雖高卻很值得嘗試，說是全港最美味的乳豬一點也不為過。

As they are charging premium price, customers will expect the same in food quality and service, unfortunately it is not the case.  Food tastes ok and service is average, so there is nothing wrong.  But you cand find the same quality and service elsewhere, probably at 2/3 or half the price!
一般的な飲茶の物も想像以上銘茶美味しくて驚くて〜次もこちらに食べます。

七福是過去福臨門的研續，理應更上一層樓，可是不思進取，不但沒有進步，還在退步，服務一曰差過一曰。
在我理解中，富豪飯堂理應服務好.、食品好味和有驚喜及新意
不能以老買老，不思進取
難道過去福臨門的名字是賣回來的
Service is great. The food all looks good but not that tasty in my opinion.

reviews.text: New room on high floor. Professional service. Great location. Breakfast totally reasonable for the price.

Watch out your credit card. Recently I was surprised to see this hotel booked 690$ from my credit card. Since I never stayed there nor booked any room I realized my credit card number was stolen as I had my physical card on me. I've contacted the hotel and they are not collaborative at all. I have second factor authentication on my card and I don't know how anyone could use it online so it could be someone from the staff involved? I don't want to accuse anyone but this hotel enjoys my 690$ and don't bother to take a look in their records who enjoy the stay. Coincidence?
Conceirge was not friendly. I appreciate the old guy/security man though. He was very helpful

Friendly and helpful staff. Complimentary free wi-fi is for one device per room only. The bath tub was too narrow and when flushing down the toilet wasn't working properly.
Free minibar hasn't been refilled after the first consumption.

The hotel is quite gold place but surroundings are not good a bit as there are pubs nearby and people drink and roam around specially the black guys follow you and abuse indians. The hotel is superb with excellent services but at a wrong location. There are nearby indian veg restaurant like khana-khazana at a walk of 15 mins and a local grocery store called 7eleven nearby to get water bottles, coffee, chocolate etc..

reviews.text: 地點很方便，不管是巴士還是地鐵都在旁邊，第一天的房間排水系統很差，還跳電，不過飯店服務人員很好馬上升級房間。對面就有全天營業的翠華餐廳，還有很多酒吧！

よかった！香港のホテルは超高級ホテルじゃないと期待出来ませんが、ここはお値段以上でした。部屋は広くないし泊まった部屋はバスタブはないけど場所が便利。近くにバーが多いのでそうゆうお店が好きな人にはおすすめです。フロントも細かいお金に両替したり不足の物をお願いしたりしても対応が早い。
あとどこにも記載がないけどミニバーが無料です。コーラやビールが飲めます。買いに行くのめんどくさい時にぜひ。
帰りのタクシーがなかなか捕まらなかったけど、ホテルの方が代わりに探してくれました。少し日本語が話せるお兄さんです。
九龍島もいいけど香港島にとまるなら次回も使いたい。
写真はホテルからすぐのお店です。

reviews.text: Great dim sum and authentic Cantonese cuisine!
Lived in HK for so many years, honestly the best Dim sum place in my opinion but it's a bit pricey

One of best cantonese cuisine restaurants I've been to anywhere in the world. The roast pig is an absolute must: note, you do need to order this in advance. The skin is perfectly crispy and not greasy since the fat is properly rendered. The meat is tender and juicy, perfect without any additional sauces. We'd also ordered the fresh crab stir fried in ginger and spring onion. The crabmeat is perfectly cooked, tender and flavorful. The service was also impeccable, on par with any michelin starred establishment. Thank you again for an unforgettable meal!

As a dim sum restaurant with a long history, Seventh Son attracts many locals as its weekend go-to place for family gatherings. The signature dish is the fried pork skin, I believe the skin has been heated with a torch to make it extra crispy on the outside yet tender on the inside. Other dish quality varies across, for example, the lotus paste and egg yolk bun was very heavy, we only managed to eat one. Egg tart was overly sweet and oily. Chicken feet and pork rib were very delicious, making the two most common stables of dim sum stand out is not an easy task, but the restaurant added it’s own spin to it. Overall, it’s a decent dim sum restaurant with a not so price-friendly menu. Tourist looking for a authentic dim sum  experience will have other better options. 

Food quality: 4 Star
Cleanliness: 5 Star
Service: 5 Star
Price: 3 Star

Overall: 3.8 Star
